ing%20the%20new%20requirements%20for%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20process%20and%20reiterating%20the%20press%20secretary's%20statement%20that%20the%20new%20rules%20do%20not%20apply%20to%20current%20visa%20holders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20and%20Lutnick%20said%20the%20executive%20order%20was%20needed%20to%20prevent%20abuse%20of%20the%20H-1B%20visa%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20at%20Amazon%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20elsewhere%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-memos-sent-big-tech-trump-h-1b-changes-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereceived%20memos%3C%2Fa%3E%20instructing%20H-1B%20employees%20to%20avoid%20traveling%20out%20of%20the%20US%20or%20to%20return%20before%20Sunday's%20deadline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20State%2C%20which%20issues%20immigrant%20and%20non-immigrant%20visas%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20it%20is%20%26quot%3Bworking%20closely%20with%20the%20White%20House%20and%20interagency%20partners%20to%20implement%26quot%3B%20the%20executive%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20everything%20you%20need%20to%20know%20about%20the%20H-1B%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2270f3eb98-b697-486b-aa0f-8e504e592d66%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20H-1B%20program%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor%2C%20the%20H-1B%20program%20allows%20employers%20to%20hire%20non-immigrants%20as%20workers%20in%20specialized%20occupations.%20Non-immigrants%20refer%20to%20people%20who%20have%20permanent%20residence%20outside%20of%20the%20US%20but%20wish%20to%20temporarily%20enter%20the%20country%20for%20work%2C%20tourism%2C%20medical%20treatment%2C%20or%20other%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20specialized%20occupation%20requires%20%26quot%3Bthe%20application%20of%20a%20body%20of%20highly%20specialized%20knowledge%20and%20the%20attainment%20of%20at%20least%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20or%20its%20equivalent%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d31c8dba-ed03-422e-943b-1ee5749b3b17%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20H-1B%20visas%20for%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Labor%20said%20the%20H-1B%20program%20can%20help%20employers%20hire%20workers%20with%20skills%20not%20found%20in%20the%20US%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20intent%20of%20the%20H-1B%20provisions%20is%20to%20help%20employers%20who%20cannot%20otherwise%20obtain%20needed%20business%20skills%20and%20abilities%20from%20the%20US%20workforce%20by%20authorizing%20the%20temporary%20employment%20of%20qualified%20individuals%20who%20are%20not%20otherwise%20authorized%20to%20work%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20agency%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d33230e6-a2e7-43de-bdf4-acdfa2d0d65e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20is%20eligible%20for%20an%20H-1B%20visa%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20Citizenship%20and%20Immigration%20Services%20said%20foreign%20workers%20are%20eligible%20for%20the%20H-1B%20program%20if%20they%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHold%20a%20US%20bachelor's%20or%20higher%20degree%20required%20by%20the%20specialty%20occupation%20from%20an%20accredited%20college%20or%20university%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHold%20a%20foreign%20degree%20that%20is%20the%20equivalent%20of%20a%20US%20bachelor's%20or%20higher%20degree%20required%20by%20the%20specialty%20occupation%20from%20an%20accredited%20college%20or%20university%3B%20or%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHold%20an%20unrestricted%20state%20license%2C%20registration%2C%20or%20certification%20that%20authorizes%20you%20to%20fully%20practice%20the%20specialty%20occupation%20and%20be%20immediately%20engaged%20in%20that%20specialty%20in%20the%20state%20of%20intended%20employment.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHave%20education%2C%20specialized%20training%2C%20and%2For%20progressively%20responsible%20experience%20that%20is%20equivalent%20to%20the%20completion%20of%20a%20US%20bachelor's%20or%20higher%20degree%20in%20the%20specialty%20occupation%2C%20and%20have%20recognition%20of%20expertise%20in%20the%20specialty%20through%20progressively%20responsible%20positions%20directly%20related%20to%20the%20specialty.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20also%20outlined%20requirements%20for%20employers%20on%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uscis.gov%2Fworking-in-the-united-states%2Fh-1b-specialty-occupations%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f29e6c32-d88f-47e9-ab36-68dc0ef76b43%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20long%20are%20H-1B%20visas%20valid%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Citizenship%20and%20Immigration%20Services%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uscis.gov%2Fworking-in-the-united-states%2Ftemporary-workers%2Fh-1b-specialty-occupations%2Ffaqs-for-individuals-in-h-1b-nonimmigrant-status%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eoutlined%20several%20scenarios%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20H-1B%20non-immigrant%20status%20on%20its%20website%2C%20so%20several%20factors%20typically%20play%20a%20role%20in%20determining%20a%20visa's%20validity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20agency%20said%20that%20for%20workers%20who%20had%20%26quot%3Bno%20pending%20or%20approved%20Form%20I-140%20or%20labor%20certification%2C%26quot%3B%20H-1B%20status%20is%20%26quot%3Bvalid%20up%20to%20three%20years%20and%20%26quot%3Bextendable%20up%20to%20another%203%20years%2C%20for%20total%20period%20of%20admission%20of%206%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22addcc9f3-bd93-4df8-875a-425154a43132%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20employers%20compensate%20H-1B%20visa%20holders%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Department%20of%20Labor%20said%20employers%20must%20pay%20foreign%20workers%20hired%20through%20the%20H-1B%20program%20%26quot%3Bat%20least%20equal%20to%20the%20actual%20wage%20paid%20by%20the%20employer%20to%20other%20workers%20with%20similar%20experience%20and%20qualifications%20for%20the%20job%20in%20question%2C%20or%20the%20prevailing%20wage%20for%20the%20occupation%20in%20the%20area%20of%20intended%20employment%20%E2%80%94%20whichever%20is%20greater.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployers%20can%20pay%20H-1B%20workers%20an%20hourly%20or%20a%20salaried%20wage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221ea7062d-b53a-4321-89c6-18a6ae17c512%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20much%20money%20do%20H-1B%20workers%20typically%20earn%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EH-1B%20workers'%20salaries%20can%20vary%20depending%20on%20the%20specific%20job%20and%20field.%20Employers%20don't%20report%20exact%20salary%20data%20for%20H-1B%20workers.%20They%20do%2C%20however%2C%20report%20typical%20salaries%20for%20roles%20held%20by%20H-1B%20workers.%20Data%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor%20shows%20what%20the%20likely%20salary%20ranges%20would%20be%20for%20H-1B%20visa%20holders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2030%25%20of%20H-1B%20workers%20make%20%24100%2C000%20or%20less.%20Nearly%2010%25%20make%20over%20%24200%2C000%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F373hq%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Bar%20Chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F373hq%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22090a729c-a2de-4719-a2bd-21e8a3d84233%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhich%20industries%20will%20be%20most%20affected%20by%20Trump's%20H-1B%20visa%20changes%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor%20showed%20that%20%26quot%3Bprofessional%2C%20scientific%2C%20and%20technical%20services%26quot%3B%20account%20for%20nearly%2050%25%20of%20H-1B%20applicants.%20Manufacturing%20ranked%20second.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FSvJ8F%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-w