%20Production%20is%20shopping%20a%20six-project%20slate%20at%20Busan%E2%80%99s%20Asian%20Contents%20%26amp%3B%20Film%20Market%2C%20with%20budgets%20ranging%20from%20%24440%2C000%20to%20%241.1%20million%20and%20production%20timelines%20stretching%20through%202028.%20The%20company%20is%20unveiling%20its%20lineup%20under%20the%20banner%20%E2%80%9CTrue%20Stories%20of%20Indonesia%3A%20From%20Local%20Roots%20to%20Global%20Screen%E2%80%9D%20at%20ACFM%E2%80%99s%20Happy%20Hour%20Event%2C%20seeking%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Naman%20Ramachandran%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2025%2Ffilm%2Fmarkets-festivals%2Findonesia-matta-cinema-slate-busan-market-1236525419%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'A%20lot%20of%20panic'%3A%20Lawyers%20race%20to%20decipher%20Trump's%20H-1B%20visa%20fees%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225729%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Donald%20Trump%20in%20the%20Oval%20Office%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68cf166d183847aa39d72e64%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223820%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20speaks%20as%20Commerce%20Secretary%20Howard%20Lutnick%20listens%20as%20Trump%20signs%20executive%20order%20in%20the%20Oval%20Office%20of%20the%20White%20House%2C%20Friday%2C%20Sept.%2019%2C%202025%2C%20in%20Washington.%3Cp%3EAlex%20Brandon%2FAssociated%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%20executive%20order%20on%20H-1B%20visas%20caused%20confusion%20for%20workers%20and%20employers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20was%20initially%20unclear%20who%20would%20be%20affected.%20The%20White%20House%20clarified%20that%20it%20was%20only%20new%20applicants.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20panic%20by%20employers%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20immigration%20attorney%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20White%20House%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fh1b-visa-trump-executive-order-what-to-know-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eorder%20on%20H-1B%20visas%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20sent%20immigration%20and%20employment%20lawyers%20scrambling%20for%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUncertainty%20over%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20order%2C%20which%20imposes%20a%20%24100%2C000%20fee%20on%20H-1B%20visa%20applicants%2C%20led%20many%20lawyers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20some%20major%20employers%20%E2%80%94%20to%20advise%20visa%20holders%20outside%20the%20US%20to%20return%20before%20the%20fee%20was%20set%20to%20go%20into%20effect%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAttorneys%20told%20Business%20Insider%20they%20struggled%20to%20advise%20clients%20amid%20the%20confusion%20caused%20by%20the%20sudden%20order%2C%20which%20was%20announced%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%20on%20Friday%20and%20which%20they%20said%20lacked%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20White%20House%20official%20told%20Business%20Insider%20on%20Saturday%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhite-house-h1b-visa-fee-status-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evisa%20changes%20will%20only%20affect%20new%20applicants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20the%20executive%20order%20issued%20Friday%20evening%20does%20not%20clearly%20state%20that%2C%20and%20Commerce%20Secretary%20Howard%20Lutnick%20initially%20said%20it%20would%20include%20current%20visa%20holders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20Saturday%20afternoon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FPressSec%2Fstatus%2F1969495900478488745%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20White%20House%20press%20secretary%20Karoline%20Leavitt%20further%20clarified%20that%20the%20fee%20would%20represent%20a%20one-time%20cost%20and%20that%20it%20wouldn't%20apply%20to%20current%20visa%20holders%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20those%20with%20visas%20who%20are%20outside%20the%20US%20wouldn't%20be%20charged%20to%20re-enter%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20panic%20by%20employers%20in%20myriad%20situations%2C%26quot%3B%20Jason%20Finkelman%2C%20an%20immigration%20lawyer%20based%20in%20Austin%20who%20has%20clients%20throughout%20the%20US%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinkelman%20said%20that%20beyond%20advising%20clients%20to%20get%20back%20to%20the%20US%20before%20Sunday%2C%20he%20has%20little%20concrete%20counsel%20to%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20issue%20these%20vague%20executive%20orders%2C%20it%20causes%20chaos%20and%20confusion%2C%26quot%3B%20Finkelman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a2accba7-4ea3-453b-93ec-84e9484acab1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20day%20of%20questions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFinkelman%20expects%20legal%20challenges%20to%20the%20order.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20said%2C%20it's%20uncertain%20whether%20prior%20Supreme%20Court%20rulings%20that%20made%20it%20harder%20for%20judges%20to%20issue%20nationwide%20restraining%20orders%20could%20complicate%20efforts%20to%20bring%20about%20a%20broad%20injunction%20by%20opponents%20of%20the%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinkelman%20also%20said%20he's%20getting%20questions%20from%20employers%20about%20what%20mechanism%20they%20would%20use%20to%20pay%20the%20%24100%2C000%20and%20whether%20companies%20would%20get%20that%20back%20if%20the%20executive%20order%20is%20reversed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20answer%20is%2C%20'I%20don't%20have%20any%20answers%20to%20that.'%20No%20one%20really%20has%20any%20answers%20to%20that%20because%20the%20guidance%20is%20not%20clear%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESophie%20Alcorn%2C%20founder%20of%20Alcorn%20Law%20in%20Palo%20Alto%2C%20California%2C%20whose%20clients%20include%20venture%20capital%20firms%20and%20small%20startups%2C%20said%20smaller%20companies%20and%20startups%20could%20be%20hit%20hard%20by%20the%20change%20if%20they%20find%20the%20%24100%2C000%20tab%20prohibitive.%20By%20comparison%2C%20she%20said%2C%20Big%20Tech%20could%20absorb%20the%20cost%20for%20some%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20bifurcating%20between%20the%20large%20organizations%20that%20can%20afford%20to%20basically%20pay%20to%20play%20and%20bring%20in%20whomever%20they%20would%20like%2C%20and%20then%20the%20small%20and%20medium-sized%20businesses%20and%20the%20early-stage%20startups%2C%26quot%3B%20Alcorn%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinkelman%20said%20there%20wasn't%20sufficient%20clarity%20around%20the%20proposed%20%26quot%3Bnational%20interest%26quot%3B%20provision%20in%20the%20order%2C%20which%20could%2C%20it%20appears%2C%20let%20companies%20sidestep%20the%20%24100%2C000%20visa%20fee.%20He%20said%20clients%20were%20asking%20how%20they%20might%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Rahbar%2C%20an%20employment%20attorney%20who%20founded%20the%20boutique%20firm%20the%20Rahbar%20Group%20in%20New%20York%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20even%20among%20the%20tech%20heavyweights%2C%20the%20cost%20would%20likely%20dissuade%20some%20hiring.%20He%20said%20that%20if%20it%20remains%20in%20place%2C%20big%20companies%20could%20shift%20work%20overseas%20to%20where%20the%20talent%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20not%20enough%20people%20in%20America%20to%20provide%20these%20resources%2C%20and%20they're%20just%20going%20to%20go%20to%20other%20countries%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20companies%20in%20search%20of%20skilled%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERahbar%20said%20that%20while%20the%20biggest%20impact%20would%20be%20in%20tech%2C%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20US%20economy%20aren't%20immune%20to%20potential%20fallout%20from%20the%20H-1B%20changes.%20He%20said%20that%20it's%20unlikely%20that%20medical%20workers%2C%20for%20example%2C%20who%20might%20not%20earn%20%24100%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20would%20have%20employers%20willing%20to%20fork%20over%20that%20amount%20to%20have%20them%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHealthcare%20workers%20represented%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uscis.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fdocument%2Freports%2Fola_signed_h1b_characteristics_congressional_report_FY24.pdf%3Futm_source%3Dchatgpt.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E4%25%20of%20approved%20H-1B%20petitions%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20fiscal%202024%2C%20according%20to%20an%20April%20report%20by%20the%20US%20Citizenship%20and%20Immigration%20Services%2C%20a%20federal%20agency.%20The%20category%20of%20professional%2C%20scientific%2C%20and%20technical%20services%20accounted%20for%2048%25%20of%20authorized%20H-1B%20visas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2264defaf0-18cd-4e77-b61b-eb5015dcd2ed%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGetting%20back%20in%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShaun%20Foster%2C%20an%20immigration%20attorney%20at%20PampaninFoster%20near%20Boston%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he's%20been%20fielding%20questions%20from%20at%20least%20a%20half%20dozen%20clients%20%E2%80%94%20including%20in%20India%20and%20Spain%20%E2%80%94%20over%20what%20the%20changes%20to%20the%20visa%20program%20will%20mean%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20the%20forthcoming%20changes%2C%20visa%20fees%20might%20have%20ranged%20from%20about%20%242%2C000%20to%20%244%2C000%20per%20case%20each%20time%20an%20employer%20had%20to%20file.%20That%20typically%20happened%20every%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fees%20that%20we%20already%20pay%20are%20substantial%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Foster%20said%20the%20fees%20had%20long%20been%20intended%20as%20a%20means%20of%20covering%20the%20costs%20of%20the%20paperwork%2C%20not%20to%20serve%20as%20revenue%20generators%2C%20or%20to%20keep%20employers%20from%20bringing%20in%20skilled%20foreign%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20said%20the%20effort%20is%20designed%20to%20dissuade%20US%20employers%20from%20hiring%20foreign%20workers%20instead%20of%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFoster%20said%20it%20was%20likely%20that%20in%20the%20Boston%20area%2C%20where%20he%20is%20based%20and%20where%20sciences%20and%20biotech%20are%20important%20economic%20drivers%2C%20the%20impact%20could%20be%20profound.%20He%20said%20it%20could%20hurt%20work%20in%20those%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20life-changing%2C%26quot%3B%20Foster%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20now%20appears%20the%20US%20is%20at%20a%20%26quot%3Bcrossroads%26quot%3B%20where%20Washington%20wants%20to%20depart%20from%20supporting%20those%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20had%20been%20writing%20weekend%20emails%20to%20clients%20in%20India%20and%20thinking%20about%20how%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20they%20would%20have%20had%20about%2015%20hours%20to%20make%20it%20back%20to%20the%20US%20in%20time.%20%26quot%3BI%20really%20don't%20know%20if%20that's%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20Foster%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20short%20notice%20before%20the%20implementation%20served%20to%20%26quot%3Bunpredictably%20sow%20havoc%20into%20the%20system%20and%20just%20cause%20everybody%20to%20have%20to%20scramble.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeon%20Fresco%2C%20an%20immigration%20attorney%20and%20partner%20at%20Holland%20%26amp%3B%20Knight%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20it's%20possible%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-employees-h-1b-visa-travel-return-trump-eo-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompanies%20urging%20visa%20holders%20to%20rush%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20US%20are%20overreacting%2C%20but%20because%20of%20the%20lack%20of%20clarity%20around%20the%20order%2C%20it's%20difficult%20for%20employers%20to%20know%20how%20to%20proceed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20is%20this%3A%20The%20wording%20is%20very%20vague%2C%26quot%3B%20Fresco%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20Tim%20Paradis%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Atparadis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Etparadis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%2