delines%20for%20infractions.%20A%20serious%20infraction%20of%20the%20rules%2C%20like%20a%20profane%20message%20or%20repeatedly%20forgetting%20to%20mark%20a%20customer's%20cup%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20termination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStarbucks%20prohibits%20the%20writing%20or%20printing%20of%20content%20on%20items%20that%20is%20inappropriate%2C%20offensive%2C%20or%20otherwise%20does%20not%20align%20with%20our%20Mission%20%26amp%3B%20Values%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20page%20from%20the%20Starbucks%20store%20operating%20manual%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPartners%20should%20also%20not%20write%20or%20print%20content%20on%20items%20that%20advocates%20for%20a%20political%2C%20religious%2C%20or%20personal%20issue%2C%20even%20if%20requested%20by%20a%20customer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20spoke%20to%2014%20baristas%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-ceo-brian-niccol-chinese-competitor-luckin-coffee-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EStarbucks%20stores%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20country%20about%20the%20policy.%20They%20had%20varying%20interpretations%20of%20what%20notes%20are%20permitted%20under%20the%20company%20guidelines%2C%20and%20said%20that%20the%20enforcement%20of%20rules%20around%20cup%20notes%20has%20intensified%20in%20recent%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20witnessed%20a%20couple%20of%20dozen%20verbal%20coachings%2C%20including%20me%2C%20because%20I%20didn't%20catch%20two%20cups%20that%20the%20barista%20making%20the%20drinks%20forgot%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Minnesota-based%20barista%20who%20has%20worked%20with%20Starbucks%20for%20seven%20years%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarbucks%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2239efd636-496c-4185-ba16-4f89ac502bbe%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDiscipline%20for%20not%20writing%20on%20cups%20%E2%80%94%20or%20writing%20the%20wrong%20thing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20unusual%20for%20a%20company%20of%20Starbucks'%20size%20%E2%80%94%20with%20more%20than%20350%2C000%20employees%20worldwide%20%E2%80%94%20to%20set%20clear%20standards%20for%20how%20staff%20should%20interact%20with%20customers%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-ceo-brings-back-ceramic-mugs-stores-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erepresent%20the%20brand%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Businesses%20often%20have%20detailed%20rules%20with%20corresponding%20disciplinary%20structures%20to%20ensure%20consistency%2C%20efficiency%2C%20and%20a%20welcoming%20environment%2C%20particularly%20in%20large%20organizations%20where%20practices%20could%20otherwise%20vary%20widely%20across%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20guidelines%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%20indicate%20that%20%26quot%3Bminor%26quot%3B%20rule%20infractions%20include%20not%20writing%20on%20every%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-ceo-brings-back-ceramic-mugs-stores-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20customer's%20cup%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20using%20a%20pen%20other%20than%20a%20Sharpie%20to%20write%20a%20note%2C%20marking%20the%20lid%20of%20a%20cup%2C%20or%20pre-marking%20cups%20before%20a%20customer%20places%20their%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedium%20infractions%20include%20writing%20pop%20culture%20or%20political%20references%2C%20drawings%20of%20animals%2C%20or%20generational%20slang.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20say%20no%20animals%2C%20because%20it%20might%20be%20taken%20the%20wrong%20way.%20But%20when%20kids%20would%20come%20in%2C%20I%20used%20to%20write%20a%20little%20cat%20or%20a%20dog%20on%20their%20cup%20and%2C%20you%20know%2C%20they%20loved%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20barista%20in%20California%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BNow%20I%20can't%20do%20that%20anymore.%20I%20might%20get%20written%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESerious%20violations%20of%20the%20rule%20are%20those%20that%20would%20likely%20violate%20other%20store%20policies%20or%20offend%20a%20reasonable%20person%20%E2%80%94%20like%20a%20barista%20writing%20%26quot%3BDiabetes%20here%20I%20come!%26quot%3B%20on%20a%20customer's%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20video%20of%20the%20barista%20declining%20to%20put%20Kirk's%20name%20on%20a%20cup%20after%20the%20conservative%20activist%20was%20murdered%2C%20Starbucks%20clarified%20that%20the%20company%20does%20not%20restrict%20what%20names%20customers%20can%20request%20on%20their%20orders%2C%20even%20if%20the%20name%20is%20political.%20Any%20other%20political%20messaging%20remains%20prohibited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20aim%20to%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-q3-earnings-report-analyst-expectations-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommunity%20coffeehouse%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20everyone%20feels%20welcome%2C%20so%20we%20have%20previously%20provided%20guidance%20to%20our%20partners%20to%20respectfully%20ask%20the%20customer%20to%20use%20a%20different%20name%20when%20attempting%20to%20use%20political%20slogans%20or%20phrases%20in%20place%20of%20their%20name%2C%26quot%3B%20Starbucks%20said%20Wednesday.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20clarifying%20with%20our%20team%20now%20that%20names%2C%20on%20their%20own%2C%20can%20be%20used%20by%20customers%20on%20their%20caf%C3%A9%20order%2C%20as%20they%20wish.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20guidelines%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20the%20first%20warning%20for%20a%20minor%20infraction%2C%20so%20long%20as%20a%20barista%20has%20had%20appropriate%20training%20and%20received%20no%20other%20recent%20corrective%20action%2C%20is%20verbal%20coaching.%20A%20second%20warning%20leads%20to%20a%20write-up.%20A%20third%20and%20final%20warning%20is%20issued%20before%20termination%20upon%20a%20fourth%20infraction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMedium%20offenses%20automatically%20receive%20a%20written%20warning%2C%20and%20serious%20violations%20receive%20a%20final%20written%20warning%20upon%20their%20first%20offense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20guidelines%20show%20that%20if%20a%20staff%20member%20makes%20a%20minor%20or%20medium%20infraction%20and%20has%20received%20a%20final%20written%20warning%20any%20time%20in%20the%20last%20year%20for%20any%20reason%2C%20they%20will%20be%20terminated%20from%20the%20company.%20Automatic%20termination%20may%20also%20occur%20if%20the%20infraction%20is%20so%20severe%20that%20a%20reasonable%20person%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bhighly%20offended%2C%26quot%3B%20such%20as%20a%20profane%20or%20lewd%20remark.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20as%20with%20many%20corporate%20rules%20across%20companies%2C%20whether%20a%20barista%20is%20getting%20a%20verbal%20or%20written%20warning%20could%20depend%20on%20their%20manager%20and%20their%20interpretation%20of%20the%20guidelines%2C%20six%20baristas%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20manager%20is%20more%20understanding%2C%20like%2C%20she's%20actually%20working%20with%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20California-based%20barista%20who%20has%20been%20at%20the%20company%20for%20a%20year%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20managers%2C%20when%20I've%20worked%20in%20other%20stores%2C%20don't%20really%20work%20with%20the%20employees%20and%20just%20kind%20of%20sit%20in%20the%20back%20and%20wait%20for%20you%20to%20mess%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20baristas%20told%20Business%20Insider%20they've%20seen%20fellow%20staff%20members%20be%20fired%20or%20quit%20this%20year%20over%20the%20cup%20note%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226686e2e4-53bf-4011-95c3-4db54e887263%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20attempt%20at%20customer%20connection%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStarbucks'%20cup%20writing%20guidelines%20were%20implemented%20as%20part%20of%20the%20company's%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrian-niccol-starbucks-ceo-one-year-road-map-report-card-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBack%20to%20Starbucks%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20campaign.%20In%20the%20company's%20Q3%20earnings%20report%2C%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrian-niccol-starbucks-ceo-one-year-road-map-report-card-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBrian%20Niccol%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20that%20employee%20engagement%20and%20customer%20connection%20scores%20have%20improved%20since%20the%20new%20customer%20service%20standards%20were%20rolled%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20memo%20to%20staff%2C%20previously%20reported%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Niccol%20described%20the%20return%20of%20cup%20notes%20%E2%80%94%20which%20were%20more%20prominent%20on%20Starbucks%20orders%20before%20the%20company%20began%20using%20printed%20order%20stickers%20nearly%20a%20decade%20ago%20%E2%80%94%20as%20part%20of%20his%20effort%20to%20bring%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-memo-handwritten-names-messages-back-to-cups-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bmeaningful%26quot%3B%20moments%3C%2Fa%3E%20back%20to%20customers'%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichelle%20Eisen%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Starbucks%20Workers%20United%20union%20and%20a%2015-year%20barista%20veteran%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20when%20she%20began%20at%20the%20company%2C%20the%20handwritten%20notes%20were%20used%20so%20that%20the%20barista%20knew%20what%20beverage%20to%20make.%20Once%20order%20stickers%20started%20being%20used%2C%20she%20said%20the%20company%20did%20%26quot%3Blose%20some%20of%20the%20personality%26quot%3B%20that%20made%20it%20popular.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEisen%20said%20that%20mandating%20baristas%20to%20write%20on%20every%20cup%20without%20exception%20makes%20the%20job%20harder%2C%20especially%20during%20peak%20hours%2C%20when%20staff%20attempt%20to%20get%20drinks%20in%20customers'%20hands%20in%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-ceo-wants-chain-to-be-greatest-customer-service-company-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efour%20minutes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20said%20that%20the%20threat%20of%20discipline%20removes%20the%20chance%20for%20meaningful%20connection%20with%20customers%20since%20baristas%20are%20only%20writing%20the%20notes%20%26quot%3Bunder%20duress.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20sincerity%20in%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Eisen%20said.%20%26quot%3BNow%20you've%20got%20a%20manager%20staring%20you%20down%20while%20you're%20making%20drinks%20to%20make%20sure%20you%20stop%20in%20between%20every%20single%20drink%20to%20write%20some%20sort%20of%20message%20with%20a%20Sharpie.%20It's%20only%20increasing%20wait%20times%2C%20and%20it%20is%20not%20helping%20with%20just%20the%20overall%20environment%20within%20these%20stores.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichael%20Goldberg%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20entrepreneurship%20and%20finance%20at%20Case%20Western%20Reserve%20University's%20Weatherhead%20School%20of%20Management%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-return-to-office-corporate-employees-4-days-a-week-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EStarbucks'%20policy%20%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20an%20example%20of%20a%20company%20rule%20that%20aims%20to%20better%20connect%20the%20business%20with%20its%20customers%20but%20is%20tough%20to%20roll%20out%20at%20the%20individual%20or%20store%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20increased%20visibility%20around%20the%20viral%20incidents%2C%20Goldberg%20said%2C%20behooves%20Starbucks%20executives%20to%20consider%20the%20question%3A%20%26quot%3BHow%20committed%20are%20you%20to%20doing%20these%20notes%3F%20Because%20I%20think%20they're%20just%20going%20to%20keep%20having%20these%20moments%20of%20tension.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20Katherine%20Tangalakis-Lippert%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aktl%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ektl%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%2