0great%20because%20providers%20are%20bilingual%20and%20thorough.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20my%20first%20child%20was%20born%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-florida-medellin-colombia-afford-life-of-luxury-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMedell%C3%ADn%2C%20Colombia%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20I%20had%20an%20emergency%20C-section%20after%20a%20long%20labor.%20My%20doula%20supported%20me%20at%20home%2C%20then%20accompanied%20us%20to%20the%20hospital%2C%20where%20I%20paid%20a%20small%20copay%20of%2053%2C000%20Colombian%20pesos%2C%20about%20%2414.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20discharge%20day%2C%20my%20husband%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20finance%20desk%20to%20settle%20the%20bill.%20Nervous%20about%20what%20we%20might%20owe%2C%20we%20learned%20that%20almost%20everything%20had%20been%20covered.%20In%20that%20moment%2C%20we%20realized%20how%20different%20childbirth%20could%20be%20outside%20the%20US.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%20comparison%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhealthcostinstitute.org%2Fhcci-originals-dropdown%2Fall-hcci-reports%2Fthe-price-of-childbirth-in-the-u-s-tops-13-000-in-2020%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20cost%20of%20childbirth%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20US%20was%20%2413%2C393%20in%202020.%20Even%20for%20those%20lucky%20enough%20to%20have%20fantastic%20insurance%20coverage%2C%20families%20typically%20pay%20several%20thousand%20dollars%20out%20of%20pocket.%20Those%20figures%20shock%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI'm%20an%20American%20who%20lived%20in%20Colombia%20for%20eight%20years%20and%20had%20all%20three%20of%20my%20children%20there.%20Each%20time%2C%20I%20received%20excellent%20care%20from%20bilingual%20doctors%2C%20and%20the%20affordability%20allowed%20my%20husband%20and%20me%20to%20grow%20our%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-household-net-worth-stocks-housing-fed-data-america-trillion-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enet%20worth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22586fdc5e-8fe2-47c6-886b-006eff9447ba%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EColombian%20healthcare%20felt%20like%20a%20warm%20hug%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202015%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20sold%20everything%20we%20owned%20and%20boarded%20a%20plane.%20Over%20two%20years%2C%20we%20lived%20in%2032%20countries%2C%20and%20when%20we%20landed%20in%20Medell%C3%ADn%2C%20we%20instantly%20fell%20in%20love.%20The%20city%20is%20called%20the%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdigital-nomad-visas-lowest-monthly-income-requirements-portugal-malta-list-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECity%20of%20Eternal%20Spring%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3B%20because%20of%20its%20mild%20year-round%20weather%2C%20with%20highs%20around%2080%20and%20lows%20around%2065.%20We%20wanted%20a%20lifestyle%20that%20was%20family-oriented%2C%20culturally%20rich%2C%20and%20affordable.%20Medell%C3%ADn%20delivered.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20city%20also%20had%20a%20thriving%20expat%20community%2C%20modern%20amenities%2C%20and%20a%20warmth%20in%20the%20local%20culture%20that%20made%20us%20feel%20at%20home.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20of%20my%20American%20friends%20who%20lived%20abroad%20returned%20to%20the%20US%20for%20childbirth%2C%20wanting%20to%20be%20near%20family%20and%20familiar%20hospitals.%20We%20chose%20differently.%20For%20us%2C%20the%20benefits%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdigital-nomad-lonely-managing-finances-save-money-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elower%20financial%20stress%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20excellent%20medical%20care%2C%20and%20accessible%20support%20outweighed%20the%20challenges%