bathroom%2C%20though%20these%20are%20more%20difficult%20to%20apply%20and%20require%20some%20scrubbing.%20Powders%20can%20also%20be%20abrasive%20on%20some%20surfaces.%20Follow%20the%20bottle's%20cleaning%20directions%20for%20instructions%20on%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompatible%20surfaces%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Always%20review%20compatible%20surfaces%20with%20each%20cleaner.%20Try%20a%20patch%20test%20on%20an%20inconspicuous%20place%20if%20you're%20concerned%20about%20damaging%20or%20causing%20discoloration%20to%20your%20tub.%20Some%20cleaners%20shouldn't%20be%20used%20on%20stainless%20steel%2C%20while%20others%20are%20compatible%20with%20all%20hard%2C%20non-porous%20surfaces.%20And%2C%20if%20you're%20lucky%20enough%20to%20have%20a%20marble%20bathroom%2C%20you'll%20need%20a%20gentle%2C%20specialized%20cleaner%20to%20avoid%20damaging%20the%20stone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIngredients%2FFormula%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECommon%20cleaning%20formulas%20include%20acids%2C%20natural%20ingredients%20like%20vinegar%20or%20baking%20soda%2C%20or%20bleach.%20Bleach%20is%20a%20heavy-duty%20bathroom%20cleaning%20ingredient%2C%20known%20to%20sanitize%20and%20disinfect%2C%20break%20down%20mold%20and%20mildew%2C%20and%20whiten%20surfaces.%20Bleach%20can%20irritate%20the%20skin%2C%20eyes%2C%20and%20respiratory%20system%2C%20since%20it's%20unpleasant%20to%20breathe%20in%2C%20so%20many%20people%20opt%20for%20other%20formulas%2C%20which%20are%20just%20as%20effective%20for%20routine%20cleaning.%20Outside%20of%20bleach-based%20cleaners%2C%20other%20sprays%20use%20surfactants%20to%20loosen%20messes%20and%20use%20citric%20or%20lactic%20acid%20to%20break%20them%20down.%20Bleach%20should%20never%20be%20mixed%20with%20acid-based%20cleaners%20or%20any%20other%20chemicals.%20For%20those%20looking%20to%20avoid%20harsh%20chemicals%2C%20plant-based%20cleaners%20use%20vinegar%20or%20baking%20soda%20for%20a%20natural%20clean%20that%20is%20safe%20around%20pets%20and%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%